benak.tomas.crimemonitor.client

Interface AsyncTaskHandler<TResult>

  • Type Parameters:
    TResult - the data type that a wrapped AsyncTask returns
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CrimeDataLoadingFragment.CrimeDataLoadingAsyncTaskHandler, CrimeDataLoadingFragment.KodUtvaruLoadingTaskHandler, CrimeDetailLoadingFragment.CrimeDetailLoadingAsyncTaskHandler, CrimeListLoadingFragment.CrimeListLoadingAsyncTaskHandler, CrimeSummaryLoadingFragment.CrimesSummaryAsyncTaskHandler, UtvarDetailLoadingFragment.UtvarDetailAsyncTaskHandler

    public interface AsyncTaskHandler<TResult>
    AsyncTaskHandler is an interface used for a class that acts as an AsyncTask wrapper.

    An implementing class acts as a notifier, listening for a certain subset of a wrapped AsyncTask lifecycle events, performing additional logic and reporting the events to the async task handler user.

    The aforementioned subset of AsyncTask API, that is to be wrapped, is:

    • AsyncTask#onPreExecute
    • AsyncTask#onPostExecute
    • AsyncTask#onCancelled(Object)

      The reasons for such added intermediate logic an implementing class represents may vary and are implementation specific.

    Author:
    Tom
